f the central concerns of feminist theologians.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aTheodicy. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / Orthodox.2bisacsh1 aGustafson, Richard F.1 aGustafson, Richard F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJakim, Boris.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691187990zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691187990423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691187990.jpg  a978-3-11-044249-6  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999c1927d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK